<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 13, 1861.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have instituted an inquiry into the
                            case of John J. Shaver, or Shaffer, as the same person is sometimes
                            called, and I learn, upon satisfactory and even conclusive evidence,
                            that he has been engaged in conveying revolvers and other articles
                            contraband of war to the insurgents, and at the same time acting as a
                            spy in their behalf. At present, therefore, he cannot be released.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, my lord, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>